              ]
            },
            "valueString": "68-year-old male with biopsy-confirmed non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC), adenocarcinoma subtype, stage IIIA (T3N2M0). Diagnosed 2 weeks ago after workup for persistent cough and unintentional 15-pound weight loss over 3 months. PET/CT shows right upper lobe mass 4.2cm with ipsilateral mediastinal lymph node involvement."
          },
          {
            "sequence": 2,
            "category": {
              "coding": [
                {
                  "system": "http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/claiminformationcategory",
                  "code": "info",
                  "display": "Information"
                }
              ]
            },
            "valueString": "Biomarker testing: PD-L1 TPS 65% (positive, >= 50% threshold). EGFR mutation: negative. ALK rearrangement: negative. ROS1: negative. KRAS G12C: negative. ECOG performance status: 1 (restricted in physically strenuous activity but ambulatory). Requesting first-line pembrolizumab monotherapy per NCCN Category 1 recommendation. 72-hour expedited review requested per CMS-0057-F oncology provisions."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
